<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="654" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-26"><hi rend="italic">October 26,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the embassy note of the 19th
                            ultimo to Mr. Adee, and to previous correspondence on the subject of the
                            tax levied on United States vessels entering and clearing from Canadian
                            ports, I have the honor to inform you that the question is still under
                            consideration and will receive prompt attention.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>